            <title>[DBUTILS-81] DbUtils.loadDriver() uses Class.forName()</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DBUTILS-81</link>
                <project id="12310470" key="DBUTILS">Commons DbUtils</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;Class.forName()&lt;/tt&gt; statement should be avoided due to potential OSGi issues - commons components are OSGi bundles!&lt;br/&gt;
The ClassLoader should be used instead to &lt;a href=&quot;http://download.oracle.com/javase/6/docs/api/java/lang/ClassLoader.html#loadClass(java.lang.String)&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;load classes&lt;/a&gt; and add a new method to pass custom ClassLoader.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
